cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper is about network telemetry, which involves collecting and analyzing measurement data from networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of programmable network devices, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) if the focus is on securing these devices. The use of sketches to reduce state in switches could be considered a data structure problem, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The joint collection and analysis of network traffic involves distributed systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a high-level language to express network traffic analysis tasks, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
